rComments: Easy A, if you get to know him, you will enjoy being in the class. Lectures are boring but if you study them then you'll be fine. He truly does try his best to keep things entertaining. A caring prof and tries to learn all of his students (even though this class size is usually pretty big), you can tell he really cares about the topic
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: One of my best classes this year. I always looked forward to the lectures by Prof Dib

I am a science student but this is the best course on culture and humanities I have ever taken at university The professor is very well informed and lectures are extremely interesting and well prepared. Those who think it is an easy elective may not do well.

Lectures are boring but it's an easy A class. However, he assumes that everyone in the class is able to speak Arabic so when he plays Arabic music, films or interviews he refuses to put English subtitles on and the section of the class that does not understand Arabic is left confused. He will also use class time to promote his own books.

He's honestly one of the best teachers Ive come across throughout my university experience. He's amazing, gives good lectures, and is very generous with his grades. You have to attend class. And also take notes of everything he says or shows on the screen. Memorize the notes and youll ace the course. It's so fun and interesting!!
Excellent professor of economic development about third world countries. Africa, Asia, Latin America with special focus on projects and plans.
Amazing professor, quiet informative and funny. Approachable to chat.

Easy class, very easy and fair professor. Don't even bother buying the textbook. As long as you show up, pay semi-attention, and write the quizzes, you are bound to do well. It's a 3 hour block to do other stuff. Easy bird.
never. again.

very easy class, just write down the notes and study them for the midterm. i didn't even read any of the books and did amazing so don't waste ur time. he's funny and very clear spoken. loves helping u out and actually wants everyone to do well. the final was a take home essay which was very easy (takes time yeah but very easy).

This prof is great in the way that he lets you know exactly how to pass the class. Only summaries posted on bright space so it is best to attend class, especially since there is a quiz after every lecture. He is straight forward and he seems to genuinely wan his students to do well which is refreshing.

A good basic course about the Arab golden age that covers early times and focuses on the period 600-1200. The professor is very fascinating with details, anecdotes, and interesting explanations. We get 3% of the final grade for a weekly quiz.

One of the best courses I have ever taken. The material is very interesting about the Arab golden age, science and philosophy. The professor is very friendly and approachable. Only one mid-term exam in class, and the final is take home. There is a very light quiz every quiz about the contents of the lecture and usually everyone scores high.
Good basic course of economic development with useful examples and applied projects.. You must read the chapter before the class

quiz at the end of EVERY class. homework took me 4 hours for 4%. he is very monotone and does not really take into account that the class is not too familiar with the topic and therefore he should not rush through the slides. decided to start the lecture from the next week because class was done a little early.
This course from Prof Dib in Microeconomics was obligatory for my degree and naturally I needed to work hard. Working in teams was the best way to go through the exams and tests.
This course of economic development is an elective but professor Kamal Dib makes it so interesting that it attracts a lot of students. No math but a lot of theories and text to read.

It helps if you know algebra and some stats as this microeconomics course assumes at least high school level of math. Otherwise, tests and exams are pretty straightforward. Professor is accessible even when there are 150 students in class.

He is a very knowledgeable man, and is passionate about what he teaches. However, you can't skip his class. If you don't like to read, and you don't like long lectures, then I suggest you don't take this class. Attendance is 15%. As long as you pay attention, you'll do fine.

I highly recommend this course on economic development theory with Professor Dib. A straightforward explanation of the developing world, debt and finance, foreign aid, and why some countries experience chronic poverty.

I am a science student and this course was an elective. It ended up being one of the most enjoyable courses I have ever taken. Some students thought it was an easy Mickey Mouse course so they took it. The fact is, you need to study and be there to pass the course. It's fascinating content and outstanding professor make it exceelent.

A great course on Modern Arab Culture that covers many important aspects. Attendance mandatory; take notes to get top marks; easy quiz at the end of the class on something that was mentioned in the lecture of the same night to maintain attention.

This is a great professor who teaches with passion and incredible knowledge of the Arab World and its culture. You will learn about history of modern Arab culture, music, literature, cinema, status of Arab women and other topics. Take if you really want to know those things. Not recommended for those who seek easy elective.

Lectures by typing in a word document and reading as he types. Does not post anything online and takes off marks for every hour of class that you miss. There is a quiz at the end of every class for participation but you only get 100% participation if you get 100% on the quiz. The level of detail required for the exams is unreasonable.

The course has two weekly classes, Fridays for grammar and Wednesdays for vocabulary, texts, and exercises. The requirements are all in the syllabus and the professor writes on the board at the end of every class the homework for the following week. The professor was always on time and always well prepared. Students who needed help got it.

Although Arabic was my heritage language, I learnt with Prof Dib that there is more to language than the spoken Arabic that we use at home. The grammar, the spelling, and the vocabulary are very important to know standard Arabic as written in books and newspapers and as spoken in news broadcasts. I am happy I have taken this course.

It is an easy course if you do the homework and attend classes. The professor was always available outside class and he helped students who did not do well by spending time with them to go over the tests and exams and improve their learning. We had spelling quizzes and vocabulary tests as well as a group presentation which was fun.

In my fourth year of university, this professor was so unprofessional, that I had to drop the course. He always comes late, and emails you the homework only a few hours before class. He docks you marks for texting and going to the bathroom too often. Make sure you teach yourself the chapter first.

Arabic is not my mother tongue, but I have learnt a lot from this professor. He does weekly quizzes and tests on vocabulary and writing, and inspires confidence to students to trust their learning abilities. I did so well in this course that I plan to take more Arabic.

This prof is the best prof that anyone could ask for. He really cares about the success of his students. 24% of the course grade is for quizzes, really easy ones that u do at the end of the first 8 classes. one midterm, one final (take home exam). He tells you exactly what you will be tested on on the exams. He also gives his cell number.
Such a great and passionate professor! He is there for the success of the students and he teaches because its what he loves to do.
There's only one midterm Final exam is a take home paper (approximately 2500 words)
The best professor .He is so nice and hilarious.

Attendance is mandatory for his classes, but definitely easy marks: basically an easy 20% for just attending. Fantastic lecturer and good marker. His guidelines are clear and gives lots of hints at what he is expecting. If you put effort in, you'll be happy with the marks. Definitely would recommend!

Very nice prof! Do the work and take it seriously and be rewarded with an A+. Don't forget to like his Facebook page! You get 20% just for attending the course.. thats how much he wants you to succeed.

Really easy to get an A+ or A in this class if you PUT in a decent amount of work. The biggest mistake some people make when taking this class is assuming its easy and just "wing it" stupidest thing to do. Kamal is very helpful and knows a lot about what he is teaching. Very friendly and approachable prof. A bit boring at times but all classes are.

Took this as part of my Arabic Major at Ottawa U and it was an introduction on Arabic literature. Prof Dib was thorough in his coverage of the various historical epochs and the important poets and writers of each period. His knowledge of European literatures, German, English, and French greatly enhanced the comparative reach of the course.

Great teacher! Kamal really wants his students to succeed. The syllabus is very clear and his assignments are easy. He's always there to answer questions. I highly recommend this class or any classes with him as a teacher!
Outstanding professor, Dr. Dib is highly recommended. Very entertaining, informative, up to date with technology, fully bilingual, friendly, open and modern, easy to communicate with.

Loved the class! Prof was enthusiastic and fair. Did not hesitate to call out on students for disruptive behaviour, which I loved. Midterm, and take home reflected content covered in class and the final paper was a pleasure to write. I would definitely recommend!
